#: ../../../advanced/observer_invocation_order.md:1
msgid "vtkObject Observers"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/observer_invocation_order.md:3
msgid ""
"Every `vtkObject` maintains a **priority-ordered** list of *observers* "
"(callbacks) that may be invoked by `vtkObject::InvokeEvent`. In practice, "
"this means:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/observer_invocation_order.md:6
msgid "**Priority:** Higher numeric priority runs first (default is `0`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/observer_invocation_order.md:7
msgid ""
"**Stable order at equal priority:** Observers with the same priority "
"generally run in **insertion order**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/observer_invocation_order.md:8
msgid "**Legacy exceptions:**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/observer_invocation_order.md:9
msgid ""
"When a **new lowest priority** observer is added, that observer is **pinned "
"to the end** of the list."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/observer_invocation_order.md:10
msgid ""
"An observer may **grab focus**; if it handles an event, remaining observers "
"are **not** invoked."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/observer_invocation_order.md:12
msgid ""
"If an application requires two observers to execute in a particular relative "
"order, then the application ***MUST*** add those observers with appropriate "
"priorities. The behavior described here is maintained for legacy "
"compatibility reasons only, and may be modified in the future."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/observer_invocation_order.md:16
msgid "Example Ordering"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/observer_invocation_order.md:18
msgid ""
"For example, adding four observers with default priority results in "
"invocation order:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/observer_invocation_order.md:20
msgid ""
"AddObserver(priority=0)  # tag = 1\n"
"AddObserver(priority=0)  # tag = 2\n"
"AddObserver(priority=0)  # tag = 3\n"
"AddObserver(priority=0)  # tag = 4\n"
"\n"
"InvokeEvent()  # order 2 3 4 1\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/observer_invocation_order.md:29
msgid ""
"Higher priorities are not pinned (they run first in insertion order). Lower "
"priorities trigger the pin-at-end behavior."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/observer_invocation_order.md:31
msgid ""
"AddObserver(priority=+1)  # tag = 5\n"
"AddObserver(priority=+1)  # tag = 6\n"
"\n"
"AddObserver(priority=-1)  # tag = 7\n"
"AddObserver(priority=-1)  # tag = 8\n"
"\n"
"InvokeEvent()  # order 5 6 / 2 3 4 1 / 8 7\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/observer_invocation_order.md:41
msgid ""
"Since observer `tag = 1` is no longer at the end, its pin is \"released\" "
"and subsequent default-priority observers are invoked in insertion order."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/observer_invocation_order.md:44
msgid ""
"AddObserver(priority=0)  # tag = 9\n"
"\n"
"InvokeEvent()  # order 5 6 / 2 3 4 1 9 / 8 7\n"
msgstr ""
